I'm crazy about you.

46:08.933 --> 46:11.402
RYAN: I'm crazy
about you too.

46:11.686 --> 46:13.529
I miss you.

46:14.981 --> 46:17.655
BRADLEY:
I miss you so much.

46:17.942 --> 46:20.786
RYAN: When are you
coming to see me?

46:22.238 --> 46:25.708
BRADLEY: What are
you doing Friday?

46:25.992 --> 46:27.835
RYAN:
Valentine's Day?

46:28.577 --> 46:32.502
BRADLEY: Oh, we could
meet another day then.

46:33.040 --> 46:35.714
RYAN:
No, let's do it then.

46:37.878 --> 46:39.880
BRADLEY:
Okay.

46:40.172 --> 46:41.765
Friday.

46:43.551 --> 46:45.474
RYAN:
Okay, great.

46:46.929 --> 46:48.772
Take care of yourself

46:49.056 --> 46:50.433
BRADLEY: All right.
Have a good night.

46:50.725 --> 46:52.022
RYAN:
You too.

46:59.400 --> 47:00.822
[closes laptop]

47:04.113 --> 47:06.036
[phone buzzing]

48:00.044 --> 48:01.341
KELLI:
I'm gonna go with

48:01.629 --> 48:03.802
the atonement theories
then, Professor Craig.

48:04.090 --> 48:05.307
CRAIG: That
sounds good, Kelli.

48:05.591 --> 48:06.763
KELLI: Hi, Ryan!
RYAN: Hey, Kelli.

48:07.051 --> 48:09.474
KELLI: I'll see you later, okay?
Bye, Professor.

48:09.762 --> 48:11.605
CRAIG:
Bye, Kelli.

48:13.057 --> 48:14.809
So how are you doing?

48:15.101 --> 48:16.944
RYAN:
I'm doing well.

48:17.395 --> 48:19.068
CRAIG: Well,
impress me.

48:19.355 --> 48:22.450
RYAN:Okay.
Well, simply put...

48:22.733 --> 48:23.905
Love hurts.

48:24.193 --> 48:26.036
It consumes us.

48:26.404 --> 48:30.329
But when it works,
it brings us immense joy.

48:32.827 --> 48:34.249
CRAIG:
And?

48:34.537 --> 48:36.210
RYAN:
And...

48:36.497 --> 48:41.378
Well, the thing is, it's so
difficult for it to work.

48:41.669 --> 48:46.891
If the purpose of love on earth
is to reflect God's love,

48:47.174 --> 48:53.022
but it causes so much suffering
and it's so difficult,

48:53.305 --> 48:55.899
then what does
that say about God?

48:56.809 --> 48:58.857
Why does God
give us love

48:59.145 --> 49:02.069
so that we can
reflect God's love

49:02.356 --> 49:06.202
if it's only to
suffer in the process?

49:07.153 --> 49:08.996
CRAIG:
Go on.

49:09.280 --> 49:11.282
RYAN: Okay.
So my goal is

49:11.574 --> 49:15.420
to remove the purpose of
reflecting God from love.

49:16.245 --> 49:18.088
I want to say
that to love without

49:18.372 --> 49:21.000
a teleological structure
of understanding love

49:21.292 --> 49:22.885
is still enough.

49:23.169 --> 49:27.015
When we love each other
we already love God.

49:28.215 --> 49:29.262
CRAIG:
Really?

49:29.550 --> 49:31.302
RYAN:
Yes, Professor.

49:31.594 --> 49:33.938
Even if a person
does not follow Christ,

49:34.221 --> 49:38.067
if he or she loves,
he or she reflects Christ.

49:43.189 --> 49:44.907
RYAN: Oh hey, Lorree!
LORREE: Hi.

49:45.191 --> 49:47.159
Do you need flowers
for your dad?

49:47.443 --> 49:50.117
RYAN: Oh, no actually.
Not today.

49:51.197 --> 49:54.246
In fact, I have my first
date ever on Valentine's Day.

49:54.533 --> 49:56.160
LORREE:
Ooh, congratulations!

49:56.452 --> 49:58.045
RYAN:
Thanks.

49:58.329 --> 50:00.582
So I'm considering
getting flowers

50:00.873 --> 50:04.127
but do you guys jack up the
prices on Valentine's Day?

50:04.418 --> 50:06.466
LORREE: No, we don't.
RYAN: Oh, okay.

50:06.754 --> 50:08.472
Good.
[chuckles]

50:08.756 --> 50:10.975
Do you sell out,
or anything?

50:11.258 --> 50:12.430
LORREE: Well,
I would get here early.

50:12.718 --> 50:14.220
Just to be sure.

50:14.512 --> 50:17.356
RYAN: Thanks for the tip.
LORREE: No problem, sweetie.

50:18.098 --> 50:19.850
RYAN: Do you have any
plans on Valentine's Day?

50:20.142 --> 50:21.314
LORREE: No, I'll
just be working here.

50:21.602 --> 50:22.979
I don't have a date.

50:23.270 --> 50:24.897
RYAN: Oh.
LORREE: It's all good.

50:25.189 --> 50:26.657
I prefer it that way.

50:26.941 --> 50:28.784
RYAN:
Oh, okay.

50:38.661 --> 50:40.629
KEVIN:
Oh, boy.

50:40.913 --> 50:43.257
RYAN: Cruising again?
KEVIN: No.

50:43.541 --> 50:44.884
Are you?

50:45.167 --> 50:46.089
RYAN:
No.

50:46.377 --> 50:48.755
In fact, I'm actually
seeing someone.

50:49.046 --> 50:50.969
KEVIN: Oh, really?
RYAN: Mh-hm.

50:51.715 --> 50:56.095
Uh... Hey Kevin, you're in
the school of psychology, right?

50:56.387 --> 50:57.980
KEVIN:
Yeah.

50:58.264 --> 51:00.437
RYAN: All right.
Can I ask you a question?

51:00.724 --> 51:02.101
Her name is Rachel,

51:02.393 --> 51:04.942
I just texted
you her number.

51:05.229 --> 51:08.028
She'll see you
for half the cost.

51:09.316 --> 51:11.068
BRADLEY:
I'd rather die.

51:11.360 --> 51:12.953
RYAN:
What? Why?

51:13.696 --> 51:15.323
BRADLEY: My parents
sent me to a therapist

51:15.614 --> 51:16.831
when I came
out to them.

51:17.116 --> 51:20.120
RYAN: They did?
BRADLEY: Yeah.

51:21.453 --> 51:25.174
RYAN: Well, she's not
that kind of therapist.

51:25.457 --> 51:28.631
BRADLEY: I just
don't wanna go.

51:28.919 --> 51:30.466
I don't wanna bring up
all of the memories

51:30.754 --> 51:35.806
I'm trying
to forget.

51:36.093 --> 51:37.936
RYAN :
Okay.

51:40.931 --> 51:42.683
ANTHONY: Why don't you
just find someone else?

51:42.975 --> 51:45.069
RYAN: Like you
did with Dat?

51:45.352 --> 51:48.151
Oh Jeff, I'm so sorry,
I didn't--

51:49.315 --> 51:50.362
ANTHONY:
Jeff knows about Dat.

51:50.649 --> 51:51.992
JEFF:
It's okay,

51:52.276 --> 51:57.123
ANTHONY: So why don't you
just find someone else, Ryan?

51:58.115 --> 52:01.039
GERALD:
Gosh, this is spicy.

52:03.329 --> 52:05.582
ANTHONY: I'm so
sick of all those

52:05.873 --> 52:08.968
"protect the family"
flyers all over school.

52:09.251 --> 52:10.423
GERALD:
What did you expect?

52:10.711 --> 52:12.554
JEFF:
I'm curious...

52:12.921 --> 52:14.844
RYAN:
What about?

52:15.132 --> 52:17.009
JEFF: Well, you're
all studying theology,

52:17.301 --> 52:19.429
why this seminary
if it's anti-gay?

52:19.720 --> 52:21.188
ANTHONY: You
don't have agree with

52:21.472 --> 52:22.769
everything the seminary
subscribes to you.

52:23.057 --> 52:24.684
We came here to
explore our beliefs

52:24.975 --> 52:25.851
about various
theological topics.

52:26.143 --> 52:28.316
GERALD: Yeah,
especially about sex.

52:28.604 --> 52:30.026
ANTHONY:
What, virgin boy?

52:30.314 --> 52:31.736
GERALD:
Anyway, I like it.

52:32.024 --> 52:33.571
I consider myself
a liberal evangelical

52:33.859 --> 52:35.953
and this is one of the best
evangelical seminaries

52:36.236 --> 52:37.158
in the
world.

52:37.446 --> 52:39.665
RYAN: And I like it
because it reminds me to

52:39.948 --> 52:42.792
appreciate my
gay buddies.

52:43.285 --> 52:45.083
ANTHONY:
Dat's calling me again.

52:45.371 --> 52:46.293
RYAN: I thought
you guys are done?

52:46.580 --> 52:49.424
ANTHONY: We are.
We're just friends.

52:50.376 --> 52:52.253
RYAN: Are you sure you're
ready to be just friends?

52:52.544 --> 52:54.137
ANTHONY:
Yes.

52:55.089 --> 52:57.057
RYAN: Jeff's really nice.
ANTHONY: I know.

52:57.341 --> 52:59.184
He's so nice.

53:02.304 --> 53:04.147
RYAN: Feeling better?
GERALD: Much better.

53:04.431 --> 53:05.899
ANTHONY: And how about you,
how are you feeling?

53:06.183 --> 53:08.231
JEFF: I'm better, thanks.
ANTHONY: Good. Good.

53:09.061 --> 53:12.110
Okay, which one of you
guys wants to drive me

53:12.398 --> 53:14.446
to my dental surgery
on Monday?

53:14.733 --> 53:15.700
JEFF:
I told you I'll do it.

53:15.984 --> 53:17.736
ANTHONY: No, no, I don't
want you to miss work.

53:18.028 --> 53:19.029
RYAN: Well, what time
do you have to be there?

53:19.321 --> 53:20.368
ANTHONY:
10:00 in the morning.

53:20.656 --> 53:21.748
GERALD: I have class.
Can't you drive yourself?

53:22.032 --> 53:24.956
ANTHONY: No, I'm
gonna be sedated after.

53:25.244 --> 53:27.997
Besides, they want
me to have a driver.

53:28.288 --> 53:29.835
RYAN: I can do it.
I'll take you.

53:30.124 --> 53:31.967
ANTHONY:
Thanks, Ryan.

53:32.334 --> 53:34.257
[sighs]

53:35.713 --> 53:37.636
Are you okay?

53:37.965 --> 53:41.890
RYAN: Yes, I'm very well.
I'm more than okay.

53:42.469 --> 53:51.321
J" Music J“

53:51.603 --> 53:53.071
EUGENE
'sup?

53:53.355 --> 53:56.404
RYAN: What do you want?
EUGENE: What?

53:56.692 --> 53:59.866
RYAN:
Well, what's up?

54:00.154 --> 54:03.158
EUGENE: I'm going
to propose tonight.

54:03.449 --> 54:05.622
RYAN: On Valentine's Day?
EUGENE: Yeah, man.

54:05.909 --> 54:08.537
RYAN: That's original...
EUGENE: Well...

54:08.829 --> 54:12.675
It will make it easier to
remember our anniversary.

54:14.126 --> 54:16.800
RYAN: The anniversary
of your engagement?

54:17.087 --> 54:18.134
EUGENE: Yeah man,
well, I mean--

54:18.422 --> 54:20.424
I plan to marry on
Valentine's Day too.

54:20.716 --> 54:24.346
RYAN: [scoffs]
Isn't it a bit boring?

54:26.305 --> 54:27.306
EUGENE:
It is.

54:27.598 --> 54:28.474
But I killed two
birds with one stone.

54:28.766 --> 54:30.188
We celebrate
Valentine's Day

54:30.476 --> 54:32.399
and our anniversary
on the same day.

54:32.686 --> 54:33.858
It's awesome.

54:34.104 --> 54:36.948
RYAN: That's...
efficient.

54:37.524 --> 54:39.117
EUGENE:
Thanks, man!

54:39.401 --> 54:41.324
RYAN:
And boring.

54:41.612 --> 54:43.455
EUGENE:
Bitch.

54:43.989 --> 54:45.912
RYAN:
You love me.

54:46.992 --> 54:48.915
EUGENE:
I do. [chuckles]

54:51.288 --> 54:53.211
Wish me luck?

54:54.249 --> 54:55.296
RYAN:
Good luck...

54:55.584 --> 54:59.339
But you don't need it,
she's gonna say 'yes'.

54:59.630 --> 55:01.473
EUGENE:
I hope so.

55:03.926 --> 55:05.644
[chuckles]

55:05.928 --> 55:07.555
RYAN: I just got out
of my last class,

55:07.846 --> 55:09.223
and I'm going to take
a quick shower.

55:09.515 --> 55:11.108
Are you on your way?

55:11.391 --> 55:14.019
BRADLEY: I can't
leave my bed.

55:14.311 --> 55:16.234
RYAN: Are you
still depressed?

55:16.522 --> 55:21.494
BRADLEY: [sighs]
Yes.

55:21.777 --> 55:22.653
RYAN: Do you want
me to come there?

55:22.945 --> 55:25.698
BRADLEY: No, no,
don't come here.

55:26.365 --> 55:28.163
RYAN:
Why not?

55:28.450 --> 55:31.670
BRADLEY: 'Cause I don't
want you to see me like this.

55:31.954 --> 55:34.798
RYAN: It's okay.
BRADLEY: It's not okay.

55:36.959 --> 55:40.884
I'm so sorry,
but can we postpone?

55:43.173 --> 55:46.177
RYAN: When, though?
BRADLEY: Next week?

55:46.468 --> 55:48.311
Saturday?

55:49.680 --> 55:52.308
RYAN: I can't. I'm seeing
my morn on Saturday.

55:52.599 --> 55:54.818
BRADLEY: Right.
Friday, then?

55:56.436 --> 55:58.313
RYAN :
Okay.

55:59.231 --> 56:01.154
BRADLEY:
I'm sorry.

56:02.609 --> 56:04.532
RYAN:
That's all right.

56:04.862 --> 56:08.412
RYAN: I'll talk to you later.
BRADLEY: Okay.

56:10.576 --> 56:12.249
[exhales]

56:17.624 --> 56:20.218
GERALD: Are you sure he
isn't just stringing you along?

56:20.502 --> 56:22.345
RYAN:
I don't know.

56:23.422 --> 56:26.346
He claims that
he misses me.

56:26.884 --> 56:28.932
GERALD:
So?

56:29.219 --> 56:32.063
Actions speak
louder than words.

56:32.639 --> 56:34.312
RYAN:
I know.

56:37.519 --> 56:39.396
GERALD:
Do you love him?

56:41.523 --> 56:43.446
RYAN:
I don't know.

56:46.528 --> 56:48.451
I desire him.

56:52.534 --> 56:54.411
I Wish I didn't.

56:54.703 --> 56:57.547
I wish I had no desire.

57:08.258 --> 57:10.181
I miss his smell.

57:17.559 --> 57:22.235
Can you believe we chatted
for a year before meeting?

57:22.522 --> 57:24.490
And when we finally met,

57:24.775 --> 57:27.369
he was everything
I expected and more.

57:28.195 --> 57:30.539
It's as if he could
read my mind,

57:30.822 --> 57:33.666
tell how I
was feeling...

57:34.242 --> 57:38.167
And I've never known
anyone like that before.

57:40.582 --> 57:43.506
I think there is
something special there.

57:45.796 --> 57:48.720
GERALD: But he
keeps postponing.

57:50.175 --> 57:53.099
RYAN: I know.
I feel so stupid!

57:56.765 --> 57:59.689
GERALD: You are
far from stupid.

58:09.611 --> 58:12.706
RYAN: I just want
to be with him.

58:16.994 --> 58:19.918
RYAN: I'm sorry.
GERALD: It's okay.

58:21.581 --> 58:24.505
RYAN: Are you okay?
GERALD: Yeah.

58:25.210 --> 58:27.429
I'm tired. I think
I'm gonna go to bed.

58:27.713 --> 58:30.182
RYAN: Seriously?
GERALD: Yeah.

58:32.634 --> 58:34.557
RYAN:
What's wrong?

58:39.057 --> 58:41.981
GERALD: Let's just
change the topic.

58:43.812 --> 58:45.439
RYAN:
Why?

58:48.608 --> 58:50.406
RYAN: Are you okay?
GERALD: He is selfish.

58:50.694 --> 58:52.241
He's toying with you,
he's insincere.

58:52.529 --> 58:54.531
He sneaks around online,
doesn't fulfill his promises.

58:54.823 --> 58:56.416
RYAN :
Okay.

58:59.327 --> 59:01.250
GERALD:
Okay.

59:02.289 --> 59:04.212
Bed time.

59:04.541 --> 59:07.465
RYAN: Gerald,
what is going on?

59:11.006 --> 59:14.931
GERALD: Please don't
act like you don't know.

59:15.761 --> 59:17.479
RYAN:
Know what?

59:17.763 --> 59:19.640
[chuckles]

59:19.931 --> 59:23.356
GERALD: Do I need
to state the obvious?

59:23.643 --> 59:25.486
RYAN:
Yes! Please.

59:28.190 --> 59:30.864
GERALD: You like
to hear it, right?

59:31.151 --> 59:32.994
RYAN:
Hear what?

59:39.826 --> 59:41.749
GERALD:
I love you.

59:44.664 --> 59:45.540
RYAN:
You love me?

59:45.832 --> 59:49.632
GERALD: You know I do.
Don't deny it.

59:50.295 --> 59:54.220
[sighs] Feels good to
say it out loud, though.

01:00:00.806 --> 01:00:02.729
I've--

01:00:03.767 --> 01:00:05.690
I've always loved you.

01:00:08.313 --> 01:00:10.236
[chuckles]

01:00:15.862 --> 01:00:17.785
Nothing to say'?

01:00:21.368 --> 01:00:23.291
It's okay.

01:00:30.085 --> 01:00:31.632
I'm going to bed.

01:00:31.920 --> 01:00:35.140
Lock the door on
your way out please.

01:00:53.608 --> 01:00:56.578
RYAN: How was
your Valentine's Day?

01:00:56.862 --> 01:01:01.459
ANTHONY: [clears throat]
Jeff was out of town. I saw Dat.

01:01:01.741 --> 01:01:03.584
RYAN: You did?
ANTHONY: Yeah.

01:01:03.869 --> 01:01:04.961
RYAN:
What did you guys do?

01:01:05.245 --> 01:01:07.043
ANTHONY: You know,
we just hung out.

01:01:07.330 --> 01:01:08.798
Saw a movie.

01:01:09.082 --> 01:01:11.926
RYAN: Did you
guys have sex?

01:01:12.878 --> 01:01:14.551
[Anthony sighs]

01:01:15.755 --> 01:01:18.258
ANTHONY: Yes.
RYAN: You're kidding me!

01:01:18.550 --> 01:01:19.517
ANTHONY:
I know.

01:01:19.801 --> 01:01:20.973
RYAN:
What about Jeff?

01:01:21.261 --> 01:01:23.810
JEFF: Hey Anthony,
it's Jeff again. Um...

01:01:24.097 --> 01:01:25.519
I was just calling to
see how you're doing.

01:01:25.807 --> 01:01:28.481
And I hope that evrything
is going well, and--

01:01:28.768 --> 01:01:30.486
Just give me a call back
whenever you get this

01:01:30.770 --> 01:01:31.441
so I'll know
you're okay.

01:01:31.730 --> 01:01:33.573
Okay'? Bye.

01:01:57.088 --> 01:02:01.013
[phone buzzing]

01:02:05.096 --> 01:02:06.564
RYAN:
Hello?

01:02:06.848 --> 01:02:09.772
JEFF: Hey Ryan. This is Jeff.
I got your number from Anthony.

01:02:10.060 --> 01:02:10.777
I hope you don't mind.

01:02:11.061 --> 01:02:13.029
RYAN: No, not at all.
Hi, Jeff.

01:02:13.313 --> 01:02:14.781
JEFF:
How's he doing?

01:02:15.065 --> 01:02:17.409
RYAN: He should be
out of surgery soon.

01:02:17.692 --> 01:02:19.535
[door opens]

01:02:23.949 --> 01:02:26.623
RYAN:
Let's get you to bed.

01:02:39.005 --> 01:02:40.177
Okay, I gotta run
some errands.

01:02:40.465 --> 01:02:42.058
But I'm gonna pick some
food up for you, all right?

01:02:42.342 --> 01:02:43.093
ANTHONY:
Aw, thanks.

01:02:43.385 --> 01:02:45.228
RYAN: All right.
Sweet dreams.

01:02:47.806 --> 01:02:50.605
LORREE: Hi Ryan,
I didn't see you come in.

01:02:50.892 --> 01:02:52.690
Can I help you
with something?

01:02:52.978 --> 01:02:54.104
RYAN: Actually,
I'm just browsing.

01:02:54.396 --> 01:02:55.693
I might need something
for Saturday.

01:02:55.981 --> 01:02:58.450
LORREE: Gotcha. Well,
just take your time.

01:02:58.733 --> 01:02:59.780
RYAN:
Thanks.

01:03:00.068 --> 01:03:02.662
LORREE: Hey, how did
your date like the flowers?

01:03:02.946 --> 01:03:05.449
RYAN: Oh, good.
Yeah, it was really good.

01:03:05.740 --> 01:03:07.583
LORREE: Good.
That's great.

01:03:10.620 --> 01:03:13.214
RYAN: Actually we're going
through a rough patch right now.

01:03:13.498 --> 01:03:15.466
LORREE: Oh, I'm
sorry to hear that.

01:03:15.750 --> 01:03:16.842
RYAN:
Yeah, it sucks.

01:03:17.127 --> 01:03:18.970
LORREE: See, that's why
I stay out of relationships.

01:03:19.254 --> 01:03:20.847
They're too much trouble.

01:03:21.131 --> 01:03:22.678
RYAN:
Tell me about it.

01:03:22.966 --> 01:03:25.810
[phone buzzing]

01:03:26.928 --> 01:03:28.100
I'm sorry. Excuse me,
I have to take this.

01:03:28.388 --> 01:03:31.733
LORREE: Don't worry about it.
I'll see you later.

01:03:32.017 --> 01:03:34.190
RYAN: Hello.
JEFF: Hey Ryan, it's Jeff again.

01:03:34.477 --> 01:03:35.603
RYAN: Hey, Jeff.
