01:03:35.895 --> 01:03:37.442
JEFF: I was wondering
how Anthony is doing,

01:03:37.731 --> 01:03:40.575
he hasn't been
answering his phone.

01:03:43.903 --> 01:03:44.870
ANTHONY:
Jeff is coming.

01:03:45.155 --> 01:03:46.748
RYAN: Oh good.
He'd been calling me.

01:03:47.032 --> 01:03:48.875
ANTHONY: Yeah.
I know.

01:03:50.035 --> 01:03:51.833
RYAN: So...

01:03:52.120 --> 01:03:52.962
Are you gonna
tell him?

01:03:53.246 --> 01:03:55.089
ANTHONY:
Yes.

01:03:56.791 --> 01:03:58.259
RYAN: And then what,
ask him for forgiveness?

01:03:58.543 --> 01:04:00.386
ANTHONY:
Yeah. Of course.

01:04:00.920 --> 01:04:01.762
RYAN :
Okay.

01:04:02.047 --> 01:04:03.890
[knocking on door]

01:04:08.345 --> 01:04:10.768
JEFF: Hey, Ryan.
RYAN: Hey, how are you doing?

01:04:11.056 --> 01:04:12.854
JEFF: Good.
RYAN: I was just on my way out.

01:04:13.141 --> 01:04:14.734
JEFF: Oh, you
don't have to leave.

01:04:15.018 --> 01:04:16.770
RYAN: Oh no, please.
I'm off the clock.

01:04:17.062 --> 01:04:18.029
It's your turn.

01:04:18.271 --> 01:04:19.864
JEFF: I'll walk you out.
I gotta smoke anyway.

01:04:20.148 --> 01:04:21.991
RYAN:
Oh okay.

01:04:22.901 --> 01:04:24.448
RYAN: Later, Anthony.
ANTHONY: Bye!

01:04:24.736 --> 01:04:28.582
JEFF: I'll see
you in a bit, honey.

01:04:30.116 --> 01:04:32.710
Sorry for bombarding
you with all those calls.

01:04:32.994 --> 01:04:34.166
RYAN: It was only
three calls, Jeff.

01:04:34.454 --> 01:04:35.876
JEFF:
Still.

01:04:36.164 --> 01:04:37.882
RYAN: Don't worry
about it, really.

01:04:38.166 --> 01:04:39.759
JEFF: Well,
thank you.

01:04:40.585 --> 01:04:43.509
RYAN: Seriously,
you can call me anytime.

01:04:44.089 --> 01:04:46.262
JEFF: Thanks. Sure you
don't wanna stay for a bit?

01:04:46.549 --> 01:04:49.723
RYAN: Oh no, I can't. I really
gotta work on my thesis.

01:04:50.011 --> 01:04:51.854
JEFF:
Okay.

01:04:53.932 --> 01:04:55.775
See you later.
Thanks again.

01:04:56.059 --> 01:04:58.903
RYAN: No problem.
Bye, Jeff.

01:05:04.234 --> 01:05:06.157
[exhales]

01:05:11.241 --> 01:05:21.094
J" Music J“

01:05:21.376 --> 01:05:26.376
J" Music J“

01:05:35.473 --> 01:05:38.352
RYAN: How can love be a
gift be a gift from God

01:05:38.643 --> 01:05:40.816
when it causes
so much pain?

01:05:41.104 --> 01:05:42.731
CRAIG: That's just
a part of it, Ryan.

01:05:43.022 --> 01:05:46.026
You have to look
at it holistically.

01:05:46.317 --> 01:05:50.163
RYAN: Yeah, but when
you suffer from love,

01:05:51.156 --> 01:05:54.000
that's all you
can do at the time.

01:05:54.284 --> 01:05:56.127
CRAIG:
Right.

01:05:56.744 --> 01:06:00.794
RYAN: So how can it
be a gift from God?

01:06:01.082 --> 01:06:02.925
CRAIG:
You tell me.

01:06:04.752 --> 01:06:06.504
RYAN:
Well...

01:06:06.796 --> 01:06:10.642
The only way I
can redeem love

01:06:11.050 --> 01:06:15.977
as a deliberate placement
by God to humanity

01:06:17.056 --> 01:06:19.980
is to use
the idea that

01:06:21.102 --> 01:06:25.983
the pain we suffer
is the same <i>as</i> God's.

01:06:26.274 --> 01:06:28.072
CRAIG:
Go on.

01:06:29.068 --> 01:06:30.991
RYAN:
Okay...

01:06:32.030 --> 01:06:36.001
Well, according to
Moltmann's "The Crucified God"

01:06:36.284 --> 01:06:40.960
he notes that God
yearns for our love.

01:06:42.499 --> 01:06:44.797
But we don't
always give it to him.

01:06:45.084 --> 01:06:47.928
And that is the
pain that God suffers.

01:06:49.214 --> 01:06:50.887
However...

01:06:51.758 --> 01:06:55.058
We will rectify
that with God, in time.

01:06:56.095 --> 01:07:02.023
But until then, it's the
pain of delayed parousia.

01:07:03.728 --> 01:07:06.481
CRAIG: So you want to
justify our suffering

01:07:06.773 --> 01:07:09.617
with God's
suffering?

01:07:10.485 --> 01:07:13.409
RYAN: Yeah.
I hope to.

01:07:14.072 --> 01:07:17.827
CRAIG: Okay. Do you
have any pages for me?

01:07:18.117 --> 01:07:19.960
RYAN:
Oh, urn, yes.

01:07:20.662 --> 01:07:22.585
Sorry.

01:07:29.170 --> 01:07:30.888
CRAIG: That--
This is it?

01:07:31.172 --> 01:07:33.015
RYAN:
Yeah.

01:07:35.134 --> 01:07:37.102
CRAIG: Okay,
Ryan.

01:07:37.387 --> 01:07:41.108
This quarter is almost over.
This isn't even halfway.

01:07:41.391 --> 01:07:42.984
RYAN:
I know.

01:07:45.770 --> 01:07:47.022
CRAIG:
Okay...

01:07:47.313 --> 01:07:49.566
Take these.
Take them.

01:07:50.149 --> 01:07:53.949
Come back next week
with 10 more pages.

01:07:54.237 --> 01:07:57.081
All right?
Now go. Work.

01:07:57.532 --> 01:08:00.456
[birds chirping]

01:08:18.176 --> 01:08:20.100
KEVIN:
Hey.

01:08:22.140 --> 01:08:24.063
RYAN :
Hey.

01:08:25.184 --> 01:08:27.937
KEVIN: How's your
dating coming along?

01:08:28.229 --> 01:08:30.027
[Ryan chuckles]

01:08:30.314 --> 01:08:33.194
RYAN: I find myself repeatedly
trying to forgive him.

01:08:33.484 --> 01:08:36.953
And hoping that
he'll keep his word.

01:08:37.863 --> 01:08:38.990
But...

01:08:39.282 --> 01:08:43.127
He's been nonresponsive
and he's postponed, so...

01:08:46.163 --> 01:08:49.087
KEVIN: Why don't
you just move on?

01:08:50.001 --> 01:08:51.877
RYAN:
You think I should?

01:08:52.170 --> 01:08:54.013
KEVIN:
I don't know.

01:08:54.296 --> 01:08:56.140
But clearly you won't.

01:08:57.175 --> 01:09:00.099
There's gotta
be a good reason.

01:09:01.720 --> 01:09:03.644
RYAN:
You're right.

01:09:05.224 --> 01:09:07.443
But I don't
know what it is.

01:09:07.727 --> 01:09:10.526
KEVIN:
I'm sure you do.

01:09:22.241 --> 01:09:24.243
[sighs]

01:09:24.535 --> 01:09:26.377
RYAN:
Because...

01:09:31.667 --> 01:09:34.591
Because I have
faith it'll work.

01:09:47.308 --> 01:09:49.231
KELLI:
Look!

01:09:51.520 --> 01:09:55.071
RYAN: Good, now you know
your suffering wasn't in vain.

01:09:55.358 --> 01:09:57.201
KELLI:
Thanks?

01:09:58.277 --> 01:10:00.200
EUGENE:
You okay, pal?

01:10:00.738 --> 01:10:02.661
RYAN:
Yeah.

01:10:03.032 --> 01:10:05.034
You guys are
in love, right?

01:10:05.326 --> 01:10:07.124
KELLI: Yeah, of course.
EUGENE: Yes.

01:10:07.412 --> 01:10:11.042
RYAN: Okay, okay, you don't
have to prove it or anything.

01:10:11.332 --> 01:10:13.334
KELLI: Ryan, what's wrong?
RYAN: Nothing.

01:10:13.626 --> 01:10:15.128
All I'm saying is that

01:10:15.420 --> 01:10:18.515
the suffering God gave
you for love was worth it.

01:10:18.798 --> 01:10:21.642
It paid off. You
found each other.

01:10:21.926 --> 01:10:23.178
EUGENE: God does
not give us suffering.

01:10:23.469 --> 01:10:25.221
That's something we
inflict on ourselves.

01:10:25.513 --> 01:10:27.106
RYAN: Yeah,
by needing love.

01:10:27.390 --> 01:10:29.108
KELLI: God's love is
more than sufficient.

01:10:29.392 --> 01:10:30.314
He provides us
with enough--

01:10:30.601 --> 01:10:32.444
RYAN:
I know, I know.

01:10:33.396 --> 01:10:35.023
But...

01:10:35.314 --> 01:10:38.238
I'm sorry, it's
just not enough.

01:10:38.526 --> 01:10:40.574
I need another human
being to love me too.

01:10:40.862 --> 01:10:44.207
KELLI: Well, then you've
never understood God's love.

01:10:44.490 --> 01:10:46.208
RYAN: Then why are you
guys getting married?

01:10:46.492 --> 01:10:48.836
EUGENE: Because God
wants us to get married.

01:10:49.120 --> 01:10:51.214
We're obedient to God.

01:10:52.039 --> 01:10:53.382
RYAN:
This is going nowhere.

01:10:53.666 --> 01:10:56.169
KELLI: Well, that's because
you don't have a valid point.

01:10:56.461 --> 01:10:59.180
RYAN: Okay. Your
obedience is to the nature

01:10:59.464 --> 01:11:02.308
that God created
within us.

01:11:02.717 --> 01:11:05.766
This nature causes
some of us to suffer.

01:11:06.053 --> 01:11:07.396
KELLI: The nature
you're talking about

01:11:07.680 --> 01:11:09.682
is a result
of the fall.

01:11:09.974 --> 01:11:12.068
RYAN: Oh, and
our all-knowing God

01:11:12.351 --> 01:11:14.069
didn't know that
the fall would occur?

01:11:14.353 --> 01:11:15.479
It wasn't part
of his masterplan?

01:11:15.772 --> 01:11:17.240
EUGENE:
It was,

01:11:17.523 --> 01:11:20.527
That's what makes
God so good, man.

01:11:20.818 --> 01:11:24.539
He gave us free will
despite us going against him.

01:11:24.822 --> 01:11:26.244
RYAN:
Okay, see that...

01:11:26.532 --> 01:11:29.376
That's what I hate
about theology.

01:11:30.369 --> 01:11:31.461
EUGENE:
What?

01:11:31.746 --> 01:11:35.296
RYAN: Theology is
justifying senseless beliefs

01:11:35.583 --> 01:11:40.214
with elaborate
pontifications.

01:11:40.505 --> 01:11:42.473
Isn't it easier
just to say,

01:11:42.757 --> 01:11:45.431
God was not good in
making us need love

01:11:45.718 --> 01:11:48.187
and hence, suffering?

01:11:51.098 --> 01:11:53.100
EUGENE:
Dude...

01:11:53.392 --> 01:11:56.236
Why are you
still in seminary?

01:11:57.522 --> 01:12:00.822
KELLI: Why are you
still a Christian?

01:12:01.984 --> 01:12:05.284
RYAN: Because my
faith isn't narrow.

01:12:06.823 --> 01:12:08.746
I gotta go,

01:12:11.369 --> 01:12:13.292
Anthony, wait up.

01:12:15.373 --> 01:12:16.124
Did Jeff forgive you?

01:12:16.415 --> 01:12:18.167
ANTHONY: Shush!
Not so loud.

01:12:18.459 --> 01:12:19.255
RYAN:
Well, tell me.

01:12:19.544 --> 01:12:21.217
ANTHONY:
Okay, he is gone.

01:12:21.504 --> 01:12:24.383
ANTHONY: I need to go.
RYAN: What?

01:12:24.674 --> 01:12:25.550
RYAN: [indistinct]
ANTHONY: No, no.

01:12:25.842 --> 01:12:27.219
ANTHONY: Look...
RYAN: Do you need to talk?

01:12:27.510 --> 01:12:31.356
ANTHONY: No, I just
need to be alone right now.

01:12:35.351 --> 01:12:44.453
J" Music J“

01:12:44.735 --> 01:12:47.329
EUGENE: Something's
up with Ryan.

01:12:47.613 --> 01:12:50.583
KELLI: Yeah, I know.
I'll talk to him.

01:12:50.867 --> 01:12:55.867
J" Music J“

01:13:04.422 --> 01:13:05.264
RYAN:
Hey, Mom.

01:13:05.548 --> 01:13:07.801
CINDY: What brings
you here, dear?

01:13:08.092 --> 01:13:10.311
RYAN: Well, it's
Dad's anniversary.

01:13:11.512 --> 01:13:15.938
CINDY: Yes, but I thought
I told you not to come.

01:13:16.225 --> 01:13:18.068
RYAN:
I know.

01:13:18.644 --> 01:13:21.523
But I really
want to go.

01:14:29.715 --> 01:14:33.140
RYAN: Hey.
KELLI: Hey, you wanna talk?

01:14:33.552 --> 01:14:36.305
RYAN:
Um... Okay.

01:14:36.597 --> 01:14:38.440
Sure.

01:14:48.234 --> 01:14:51.363
KELLI: Do you wanna go watch
a movie with me and Eugene?

01:14:51.654 --> 01:14:52.871
RYAN:
Yeah, okay.

01:14:53.155 --> 01:14:54.452
As long as it's
not depressing.

01:14:54.740 --> 01:14:57.334
KELLI: Of course.
How's next Thursday sound?

01:14:58.536 --> 01:15:00.459
RYAN:
Yeah, that's fine.

01:15:05.668 --> 01:15:07.966
KELLI:
Ryan, are you okay?

01:15:10.089 --> 01:15:11.887
RYAN:
No, actually, I'm not.

01:15:12.174 --> 01:15:14.017
KELLI:
Why'?

01:15:15.636 --> 01:15:17.559
RYAN: It's this
fucking thesis.

01:15:18.639 --> 01:15:20.607
I know I want
to do a good job

01:15:20.891 --> 01:15:22.859
I know I want
to go to Yale.

01:15:23.144 --> 01:15:25.522
And I know I
want to teach.

01:15:25.813 --> 01:15:27.406
But I'm just
not motivated.

01:15:28.607 --> 01:15:30.359
KELLI:
I'm sorry, Ryan.

01:15:30.651 --> 01:15:32.324
RYAN:
It's okay.

01:15:32.611 --> 01:15:35.455
KELLI: Is there anything
outside bothering you?

01:15:37.783 --> 01:15:39.706
RYAN: Outside?
KELLI: Yeah.

01:15:42.038 --> 01:15:43.756
RYAN: Like what?
Outside what?

01:15:44.040 --> 01:15:46.384
KELLI:
I mean, romantically.

01:15:46.667 --> 01:15:48.510
RYAN:
Romantically?

01:15:48.878 --> 01:15:51.882
KELLI: Yeah, are
you seeing anyone?

01:15:52.173 --> 01:15:53.550
RYAN: Am I?
I don't know.

01:15:53.841 --> 01:15:56.594
KELLI: What do you
mean, you don't know?

01:15:56.886 --> 01:15:59.389
RYAN: I just--
I don't know.

01:15:59.680 --> 01:16:02.524
KELLI:
Well, who is she?

01:16:07.521 --> 01:16:10.445
RYAN: Actually,
if you must know,

01:16:11.275 --> 01:16:12.572
his name is Bradley

01:16:12.860 --> 01:16:15.454
and he is supposed to
come see me tonight.

01:16:17.740 --> 01:16:19.413
KELLI:
So you're gay?

01:16:20.326 --> 01:16:22.249
RYAN:
Yup.

01:16:23.746 --> 01:16:25.043
KELLI:
You know...

01:16:25.331 --> 01:16:28.710
When I was with Eugene,
I was attracted to a girl once

01:16:29.001 --> 01:16:30.969
but thankfully I didn't
make that choice.

01:16:31.253 --> 01:16:32.846
RYAN: It's not
a choice, Kelli.

01:16:33.130 --> 01:16:34.177
It's God's creation.

01:16:34.465 --> 01:16:36.593
KELLI: Adam and Eve
were God's creation.

01:16:36.884 --> 01:16:37.726
RYAN: Okay, you
should know better

01:16:38.010 --> 01:16:38.886
than to argue
from Genesis.

01:16:39.178 --> 01:16:41.647
KELLI: And what
about Romans...?

01:16:41.931 --> 01:16:43.023
RYAN: Did it
ever occur to you

01:16:43.307 --> 01:16:44.433
that Paul just might
be wrong sometimes?

01:16:44.725 --> 01:16:47.569
KELLI: No, Ryan!
You are backsliding.

01:16:47.937 --> 01:16:49.484
[Ryan scoffs]

01:16:49.772 --> 01:16:51.615
RYAN:
Nice one, Kelli.

01:16:57.196 --> 01:16:59.119
KELLI:
I still love you.

01:17:02.368 --> 01:17:04.291
RYAN:
I love you too, sister.

01:17:30.229 --> 01:17:33.108
[ringing]

01:17:36.819 --> 01:17:38.947
BRADLEY: Hi.
RYAN: Hey.

01:17:39.238 --> 01:17:40.205
BRADLEY:
How are you?

01:17:40.489 --> 01:17:41.536
RYAN:
I'm good.

01:17:41.824 --> 01:17:44.668
I was just wondering when
you're gonna get here.

01:17:44.952 --> 01:17:46.920
BRADLEY: Can we
please postpone?

01:17:47.746 --> 01:17:49.669
RYAN:
What? Why?

01:17:53.502 --> 01:17:54.719
BRADLEY:
I'm just not happy.

01:17:55.004 --> 01:17:58.474
And I'm not good to
be around right now.

01:17:58.757 --> 01:18:01.556
RYAN: Well, when will
you be good to be around?

01:18:01.844 --> 01:18:03.687
BRADLEY:
I don't know.

01:18:05.723 --> 01:18:07.725
RYAN:
Look...

01:18:08.017 --> 01:18:10.736
Am I ever gonna
see you again?

01:18:11.020 --> 01:18:12.237
BRADLEY:
I hope so.

01:18:12.521 --> 01:18:14.364
RYAN:
You hope so?

01:18:16.692 --> 01:18:18.444
Bradley...

01:18:18.736 --> 01:18:21.580
I don't know how much
more of this I can take.

01:18:21.906 --> 01:18:23.579
BRADLEY:
I'm sorry.

01:18:23.991 --> 01:18:26.915
Please don't give me
any more stress.

01:18:28.621 --> 01:18:31.545
RYAN: I just want to know
if we'll ever meet again.

01:18:31.832 --> 01:18:33.175
BRADLEY: I'm gonna
start crying again,

01:18:33.459 --> 01:18:35.678
can we please
talk later?

01:18:37.880 --> 01:18:39.553
RYAN :
Okay.

01:19:55.582 --> 01:19:56.959
GERALD:
Hey, this is Gerald.

01:19:57.251 --> 01:19:59.128
Leave me a message and
I'll call you right back.

01:19:59.420 --> 01:20:01.263
RYAN:
Hey, Gerald.

01:20:03.799 --> 01:20:05.722
It's over with Bradley.

01:20:06.969 --> 01:20:08.642
I'm done.

01:20:09.263 --> 01:20:11.186
I feel like shit.

01:21:02.858 --> 01:21:12.711
J" Music J“

01:21:12.993 --> 01:21:22.755
J" Music J“

01:21:23.045 --> 01:21:32.727
J" Music J“

01:21:33.013 --> 01:21:38.013
J" Music J“

01:21:45.401 --> 01:21:48.245
RYAN: Mom?
CINDY: Yes, dear?

01:21:49.947 --> 01:21:52.200
RYAN: Did you ever
think of finding somebody?

01:21:52.491 --> 01:21:54.243
CINDY:
Finding somebody?

01:21:54.535 --> 01:21:56.378
RYAN:
Yeah.

01:21:57.955 --> 01:22:00.925
CINDY: Who wants to
date an old hag like me?

01:22:01.208 --> 01:22:02.801
[laughter]

01:22:03.085 --> 01:22:05.554
RYAN:I don't know.
Older gentlemen?

01:22:08.132 --> 01:22:10.055
[laughter]

01:22:12.136 --> 01:22:15.060
RYAN: Don't you
miss having a partner?

01:22:15.931 --> 01:22:19.526
CINDY: I do, but when
I think of a partner,

01:22:19.810 --> 01:22:22.233
I still think of your Dad.

01:22:24.773 --> 01:22:26.696
Why do you ask?

01:22:28.026 --> 01:22:29.949
RYAN:
Nothing, just wondering.

01:22:31.363 --> 01:22:35.288
CINDY: I'm fine.
Just worry about yourself.

01:22:41.039 --> 01:22:43.963
RYAN: Bye, Mom.
CINDY: Bye, sweetie.

01:22:49.006 --> 01:22:50.929
[locks door]

01:24:35.279 --> 01:24:36.952
[groans]

01:24:46.415 --> 01:24:49.760
[breathing heavily]

01:24:52.754 --> 01:24:55.257
[water running]

01:25:07.936 --> 01:25:09.813
[exhales]

01:25:22.326 --> 01:25:23.999
[turns on shower]

01:25:57.986 --> 01:25:59.909
[knocking on door]

01:26:00.906 --> 01:26:02.158
GERALD: Ryan,
are you here?

01:26:02.449 --> 01:26:04.042
RYAN:
Yes, I'm here.

01:26:05.160 --> 01:26:07.083
GERALD:
How are you?

01:26:07.954 --> 01:26:09.877
RYAN:
I finished my thesis.

01:26:10.165 --> 01:26:12.133
GERALD: Already?
RYAN: Yes.

01:26:12.417 --> 01:26:14.135
Celebrate with me'?

01:26:14.419 --> 01:26:15.170
GERALD:
Okay.

01:26:15.462 --> 01:26:17.055
RYAN:
Really?

01:26:17.714 --> 01:26:21.639
Gerald, you've always
been so nice to me.

01:26:22.177 --> 01:26:25.101
GERALD: Well, the
secret is out. [chuckles]

01:26:29.976 --> 01:26:33.856
You know how jealous
I was of Bradley?

01:26:36.233 --> 01:26:38.156
RYAN:
Kiss me.

01:26:39.653 --> 01:26:41.451
GERALD:
Kiss you?

01:26:41.738 --> 01:26:43.832
RYAN:
Yes, please.

01:26:44.408 --> 01:26:46.502
RYAN: Kiss me.
GERALD: Are you sure?

01:26:46.785 --> 01:26:48.207
RYAN: [whispering]
Yes.

01:26:49.538 --> 01:26:53.042
GERALD: You know,
I want to so badly.

01:27:28.452 --> 01:27:30.375
[exhales]

01:27:30.746 --> 01:27:33.295
RYAN:
You smell so good.

01:27:45.218 --> 01:27:48.142
Why aren't you
kissing me back?

01:27:51.016 --> 01:27:52.939
Well...'?

01:27:54.978 --> 01:27:58.858
GERALD: Because if
Bradley called you right now...

01:28:00.150 --> 01:28:03.074
You'd leave
me to see him.

01:28:03.361 --> 01:28:05.284
RYAN: He wouldn't call.
It's been three weeks.

01:28:05.572 --> 01:28:08.416
GERALD:
But what if he did?

01:28:18.543 --> 01:28:20.716
RYAN:
Please don't go.

01:28:23.632 --> 01:28:25.100
Please, Gerald.
Please.

01:28:25.383 --> 01:28:27.226
GERALD:
I'm sorry.

01:28:30.305 --> 01:28:32.103
RYAN:
Gerald, please.

01:28:32.390 --> 01:28:38.864
GERALD: I need to not see
you for the sake of my sanity.

01:28:39.147 --> 01:28:42.993
You are not the only
one suffering, Ryan.

01:29:10.846 --> 01:29:12.769
RYAN:
My thesis.

01:29:13.139 --> 01:29:15.062
CRAIG:
The whole thing?

01:29:16.393 --> 01:29:18.316
RYAN:
Yep.

01:29:19.855 --> 01:29:21.357
CRAIG: Well, I knew
you would deliver

01:29:21.648 --> 01:29:24.151
but I wasn't
expecting it this soon.

01:29:24.442 --> 01:29:27.116
RYAN: It's due in
two weeks anyway.

01:29:27.404 --> 01:29:29.702
CRAIG:
How did you do it?

01:29:29.990 --> 01:29:32.914
RYAN: Well, I haven't
really slept much.

01:29:33.201 --> 01:29:35.044
CRAIG:
I see.

01:29:35.871 --> 01:29:38.966
We didn't even
discuss your conclusion.

01:29:39.249 --> 01:29:41.092
RYAN:
I know.

01:29:43.336 --> 01:29:46.010
CRAIG:
So how does it end?

01:29:46.298 --> 01:29:51.395
RYAN: Well, I concluded that
love necessitates relationships

01:29:51.678 --> 01:29:55.273
And relationships
necessitates forgiveness.

01:29:55.974 --> 01:29:58.193
At the end of the day,

01:29:58.476 --> 01:29:59.853
we have to learn
to forgive those

01:30:00.145 --> 01:30:02.819
that we are in a
relationship with.

01:30:03.106 --> 01:30:04.949
Including God.

01:30:09.362 --> 01:30:11.160
CRAIG:
Ryan?

01:30:11.448 --> 01:30:13.291
RYAN:
Yeah?

01:30:13.825 --> 01:30:16.749
CRAIG: Are you
dating someone?

01:30:17.120 --> 01:30:19.168
RYAN:
Why do you ask?

01:30:19.456 --> 01:30:21.379
CRAIG: Well, to be
perfectly honest with you,

01:30:21.666 --> 01:30:25.387
Someone mentioned that
you might be dating a guy.

01:30:25.670 --> 01:30:27.968
RYAN:
Who said that?

01:30:28.256 --> 01:30:29.473
CRAIG:
That's not important.

01:30:29.758 --> 01:30:33.604
I told that person
to keep it to herself.

01:30:34.429 --> 01:30:36.272
RYAN:
Was it Kelli?

01:30:36.556 --> 01:30:39.184
CRAIG: What's
crucial though, Ryan

01:30:39.476 --> 01:30:42.400
is that you also
keep it to yourself.

01:30:42.687 --> 01:30:42.778
RYAN:
I know.

01:30:45.482 --> 01:30:48.201
CRAIG: You're a bright student,
have a lot of promise.

01:30:48.485 --> 01:30:52.331
I don't want to see you
get into any trouble.

01:30:52.614 --> 01:30:54.366
